# Force LF for files that are interpreted inside Linux containers or by a POSIX
# shell. Without this, a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) gives these files
# CRLF endings; when such a script is COPYed into a Linux image its shebang
# becomes `#!/bin/sh\r`, so the kernel looks for an interpreter literally named
# `/bin/sh\r`, can't find it, and the container exits 127 ("not found").
#
# Scoped to container-interpreted file types on purpose, to avoid renormalizing
# the whole tree in an unrelated change.
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
*.conf      text eol=lf
